00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:59,660
(Farance hears ghostly voices
of his medical school doctors)

790
00:41:59,660 --> 00:42:02,030
- [doctor's voices]
Make the incision, Mr. Wur.

791
00:42:02,030 --> 00:42:02,870
- [doctor's voices]
The incision...

792
00:42:02,870 --> 00:42:04,430
- [doctor's voices]
Make the incision, Mr. Wur...

793
00:42:04,430 --> 00:42:05,950
- [doctor's voices]
Cut the flesh, Mr. Wur...

794
00:42:05,950 --> 00:42:06,780
-The incision...

795
00:42:06,780 --> 00:42:08,290
-Make the incision, Mr. Wur...

796
00:42:08,290 --> 00:42:10,080
-I assure you...he's quite dead, Mr. Wur...

797
00:42:10,080 --> 00:42:12,480
-He's definitely dead, Mr. Wur...

798
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:13,360
-Quite dead...

799
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,830
-Quite dead, Mr. Wur...

800
00:42:14,830 --> 00:42:16,980
-We are all waiting, Mr. Wur...

801
00:42:16,980 --> 00:42:20,400
-Are you ready to make
the incision, Mr. Wur?

802
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:23,140
-Make the incision, Mr. Wur...

803
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:25,730
-The incision...The incision...
The incision...The incision...

804
00:42:25,730 --> 00:42:27,890
(knocking)
(ominous music fades)

805
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:43,870
(bat thuds)

806
00:42:44,490 --> 00:42:45,200
- Carmen.

807
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,910
- Hi, Farance...Mind if I come in?

808
00:42:46,910 --> 00:42:48,330
- No.

809
00:42:50,080 --> 00:42:52,440
- Hey, you fixed up the place
since I was last here.

810
00:42:53,420 --> 00:42:55,130
- I fixed the refrigerator.

811
00:42:55,130 --> 00:42:56,550
Want a beer?

812
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:59,110
- Well, it's a little bit early, but...

813
00:42:59,110 --> 00:43:01,390
sure, Farance...I'll have a beer.

814
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:10,190
(ominous music)

815
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:18,490
(ominous music)

816
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:23,620
You know, you shouldn't drink
too much beer being on medication.

817
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:26,580
(ominous music)

818
00:43:30,500 --> 00:43:32,670
- It's okay...

819
00:43:32,670 --> 00:43:34,090
I don't over do it.

820
00:43:34,670 --> 00:43:36,300
- Thanks.

821
00:43:41,470 --> 00:43:43,470
This is frozen, Farance...

822
00:43:43,470 --> 00:43:45,470
I think you're set it a little high.

823
00:43:45,470 --> 00:43:46,720
- No, don't!

824
00:43:47,060 --> 00:43:48,300
- [Carmen] Don't worry...

825
00:43:48,300 --> 00:43:49,600
I'm not going to break it...

826
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:51,140
just change the setting.

827
00:43:51,140 --> 00:43:52,650
(ominous music)

828
00:43:52,650 --> 00:43:53,980
Farance...

829
00:43:53,980 --> 00:43:56,920
You haven't been taking
your medication, have you?

830
00:43:57,970 --> 00:44:01,070
You know, it's very dangerous
to go on and off these drugs...

831
00:44:01,070 --> 00:44:03,710
You could start having
hallucinations again.

832
00:44:03,710 --> 00:44:06,240
(pills rattling)
(ominous music fades)

833
00:44:11,330 --> 00:44:13,830
- So, is this a professional visit?

834
00:44:13,830 --> 00:44:15,710
- I worry about you Farance.

835
00:44:15,710 --> 00:44:17,710
- I can take care of myself.

836
00:44:18,340 --> 00:44:20,550
- What am I gonna do with you?

837
00:44:20,550 --> 00:44:23,380
You did leave those flowers
the other night, didn't you?

838
00:44:24,470 --> 00:44:25,970
You're very sweet...

839
00:44:25,970 --> 00:44:28,720
but you know I can't become
involved with a patient.

840
00:44:29,020 --> 00:44:30,930
- I'm not a patient anymore!

841
00:44:30,930 --> 00:44:33,400
[Carmen] Oh, Farance....

842
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:35,400
- Oh, Gosh...

843
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:38,190
Look, I gotta get going...

844
00:44:38,190 --> 00:44:40,530
You've just got to stop
following me around...

845
00:44:40,530 --> 00:44:42,580
You're only hurting yourself.

846
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:46,510
Take care...

847
00:44:50,540 --> 00:44:52,440
I'll see you at work, okay?

848
00:44:53,370 --> 00:44:55,420
- Okay.

849
00:44:58,710 --> 00:45:00,550
(suspenseful music)

850
00:45:00,550 --> 00:45:02,720
- What's goin' on, Lavinia?

851
00:45:02,970 --> 00:45:06,390
- Martin, Dr. Benderfax
is still in the lab, isn't he?

852
00:45:06,550 --> 00:45:08,930
- He's been in there all afternoon...

853
00:45:08,930 --> 00:45:10,770
I thought you'd be stopping' by...

854
00:45:10,770 --> 00:45:12,140
for a little visit.

855
00:45:12,400 --> 00:45:15,730
- You're not paid to think, Martin...

856
00:45:15,730 --> 00:45:18,860
and you shouldn't be
leaving the lab unguarded.

857
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:24,000
(Andrew breathing heavily)
(distant sleepy piano)

858
00:45:24,730 --> 00:45:26,110
(sneezes)

859
00:45:26,110 --> 00:45:29,990
- [Martin] I'm not paid to do a lot
of the things I do around here...

860
00:45:30,010 --> 00:45:33,870
Just thought you'd be interested in
what Benderfax has his fingers in today.

861
00:45:33,870 --> 00:45:38,130
- I thought you said you didn't know
or care what goes on in the lab.

862
00:45:38,590 --> 00:45:41,500
- [Martin] Doesn't take a
freakin' genius to figure it out.

863
00:45:41,590 --> 00:45:43,050
- What are you getting at?

864
00:45:43,630 --> 00:45:48,140
- [Martin] Benderfax has been cutting'
on that new stroker since yesterday...

865
00:45:48,140 --> 00:45:51,350
Probably has her all over his lab by now.

866
00:45:51,350 --> 00:45:53,730
- Martin!

867
00:45:53,730 --> 00:45:55,270
- Might even have her...

868
00:45:55,270 --> 00:45:57,810
mutilated beyond recognition.

869
00:45:57,810 --> 00:45:59,940
- Martin, this isn't the time...

870
00:45:59,940 --> 00:46:02,610
or the place for this discussion.

871
00:46:02,610 --> 00:46:05,280
(suspenseful music)

872
00:46:05,280 --> 00:46:08,660
- So, let's go someplace else.

873
00:46:12,910 --> 00:46:16,210
(intense music)

874
00:46:16,540 --> 00:46:20,170
(electronic beeps)

875
00:46:31,180 --> 00:46:34,850
(machinery beeps)
(intense music)

876
00:46:47,700 --> 00:46:51,410
(electronic beeps)
(intense music)

877
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,910
(life-signs monitor beeps)
(intense music)

878
00:47:10,970 --> 00:47:13,350
(etherial music)

879
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:20,060
(music fades)

880
00:47:27,030 --> 00:47:30,360
(machinery quietly beeps)
(distant running water)

881
00:47:51,300 --> 00:47:53,390
- Wilma.

882
00:47:53,390 --> 00:47:57,430
(running water)

883
00:47:57,430 --> 00:47:59,230
(sighs)

884
00:47:59,230 --> 00:48:00,520
(louder running water)

885
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:03,400
[Dr. Benderfax singing in shower]
♪ Now that we are one ♪

886
00:48:03,400 --> 00:48:06,570
♪ Life has just begun ♪

887
00:48:06,570 --> 00:48:08,150
♪ Now you've got that glow ♪

888
00:48:08,150 --> 00:48:09,900
♪ That lovers only show ♪

889
00:48:09,900 --> 00:48:12,860
♪ When it's the right one ♪

890
00:48:12,860 --> 00:48:15,870
♪ Now that love is true ♪

891
00:48:15,870 --> 00:48:18,950
♪ I'm no longer blue ♪

892
00:48:18,950 --> 00:48:20,410
♪ And forever more ♪

893
00:48:20,410 --> 00:48:21,920
♪ I will keep in store ♪

894
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:25,250
♪ The memory of you ♪

895
00:48:25,250 --> 00:48:28,420
♪ Everything is fine ♪

896
00:48:28,420 --> 00:48:31,470
♪ Water tastes like wine ♪

897
00:48:31,470 --> 00:48:32,720
♪ Even when it rains ♪

898
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:34,300
♪ The sun shines on again ♪

899
00:48:34,300 --> 00:48:37,700
♪ It happens every time ♪

900
00:48:38,930 --> 00:48:41,270
(police station phones ring)

901
00:48:42,890 --> 00:48:44,150
(Detective sighs)

902
00:48:44,520 --> 00:48:46,690
- Can I offer you some coffee, Doctor?

903
00:48:46,860 --> 00:48:49,280
- Uh, no...Thank you, Detective.

904
00:48:52,700 --> 00:48:56,540
- These allegations about
Dr. Benderfax are very serious...

905
00:48:56,540 --> 00:48:59,990
Benderfax is a well known man in this area...

906
00:48:59,990 --> 00:49:02,830
Are you sure you want to pursue this?

907
00:49:02,830 --> 00:49:04,920
- Those incisions could
only have been made...

908
00:49:04,920 --> 00:49:07,130
while that woman was alive, Detective...

909
00:49:07,390 --> 00:49:09,210
Someone has got to stop Benderfax...

910
00:49:09,210 --> 00:49:11,420
It's obvious that he's gone mad!

911
00:49:11,550 --> 00:49:13,420
- I'd like to believe you, Doctor...

912
00:49:13,420 --> 00:49:15,020
I truly would...

913
00:49:16,300 --> 00:49:17,760
You see...?

914
00:49:17,760 --> 00:49:20,890
I had a run in with Benderfax once, myself.
(sad piano music)

915
00:49:20,890 --> 00:49:21,890
- Oh?

916
00:49:21,890 --> 00:49:23,560
- Yep...

917
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:27,310
A few years back...
I had an old dog named, Murphy...

918
00:49:27,310 --> 00:49:29,020
It may sound sentimental...

919
00:49:29,020 --> 00:49:31,690
but I really loved that dog...

920
00:49:31,690 --> 00:49:33,190
He wasn't very intelligent...

921
00:49:33,190 --> 00:49:35,480
but he had spirit...
You know what I mean?

922
00:49:35,780 --> 00:49:39,280
One time, I had to go out of town
for a couple of weeks on business...

923
00:49:39,280 --> 00:49:40,370
When I came back...

924
00:49:40,370 --> 00:49:41,540
Murphy was gone...

925
00:49:41,540 --> 00:49:43,870
Got out of the yard, somehow...

926
00:49:43,870 --> 00:49:46,170
There was a letter from
the pound in the mailbox...

927
00:49:46,170 --> 00:49:48,460
They picked him up...
so I went down to bail him out...

928
00:49:48,460 --> 00:49:50,360
But they said it was too late!

929
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:52,340
The pound said he'd been sold...

930
00:49:52,340 --> 00:49:54,590
to a laboratory for research...

931
00:49:54,590 --> 00:49:57,190
The Benderfax Institute...

932
00:49:57,680 --> 00:50:00,260
Benderfax refused to
sell Murphy back to me...

933
00:50:00,260 --> 00:50:02,720
There was nothing I could do...

934
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:03,810
Yep...

935
00:50:03,810 --> 00:50:06,100
I still think about him sometimes...

936
00:50:06,100 --> 00:50:08,980
being tortured in some dark laboratory...

937
00:50:08,980 --> 00:50:13,150
finishing out his life a part
of some sadistic experiment!

938
00:50:13,150 --> 00:50:16,490
Oh, I've been waiting for an excuse
to check out Benderfax's lab...

939
00:50:16,490 --> 00:50:18,110
for a long time.

940
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:21,370
- So, you will investigate Benderfax?

941
00:50:22,660 --> 00:50:24,450
- No, Doctor...I'm afraid not.

942
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:25,960
- What?

943
00:50:27,290 --> 00:50:30,000
- As much as I'd like to...
there just isn't enough evidence...

944
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:33,170
I could lose my badge for
throwing around accusations about...

945
00:50:33,170 --> 00:50:36,520
Benderfax doing human experiments...

946
00:50:36,520 --> 00:50:37,970
Sorry...

947
00:50:37,970 --> 00:50:39,220
Thanks for coming in.

948
00:50:40,090 --> 00:50:41,930
- What...what?...That's it???

949
00:50:41,930 --> 00:50:43,770
- I'm afraid so...

950
00:50:43,770 --> 00:50:45,180
If you get any hard evidence...

951
00:50:45,180 --> 00:50:46,850
we can talk so some more.

952
00:50:46,850 --> 00:50:48,890
- Like what for instance?

953
00:50:50,350 --> 00:50:52,650
- Like a corpse.

954
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:57,610
(suspenseful music)

955
00:51:08,290 --> 00:51:10,080
(electronic static)
(music fades)

956
00:51:11,040 --> 00:51:13,130
- I seem to remember putting you in charge...

957
00:51:13,130 --> 00:51:15,460
of security at this facility, Lavinia...

958
00:51:15,630 --> 00:51:20,050
but apparently you and Martin...
consider screwing in the supply closet...

959
00:51:20,050 --> 00:51:22,300
a little bit more important!

960
00:51:22,350 --> 00:51:24,220
I could've expected this kind of behavior...

961
00:51:24,220 --> 00:51:26,470
from that cretinous thug...

962
00:51:26,720 --> 00:51:28,850
but never from you.

963
00:51:28,850 --> 00:51:32,020
- Perhaps, if you'd screened your
new applicants more carefully...

964
00:51:32,020 --> 00:51:34,020
you wouldn't be in this predicament.

965
00:51:35,530 --> 00:51:37,940
- Yes, I've made some errors of judgment...

966
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:40,240
Blitz, and now, March...

967
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:43,070
I'm beginning to wonder whether
any of these new doctors...

968
00:51:43,070 --> 00:51:44,990
is worth a damn!

969
00:51:44,990 --> 00:51:46,790
- What are you going to do?

970
00:51:47,450 --> 00:51:49,370
(suspenseful music)

971
00:51:49,370 --> 00:51:53,640
- I've sent Martin to tidy up a few loose ends...

972
00:51:53,640 --> 00:51:55,750
If he follows my instructions...

973
00:51:55,750 --> 00:51:57,420
we may be able to resolve...

974
00:51:57,420 --> 00:51:59,670
an unfortunate situation...

975
00:51:59,670 --> 00:52:02,760
before it gets out of hand.

976
00:52:08,850 --> 00:52:11,100
- I don't want to hear any more, Andrew...

977
00:52:11,100 --> 00:52:12,870
I can't be a part of this.

978
00:52:12,870 --> 00:52:15,310
- Carmen, you didn't see what I saw.

979
00:52:15,610 --> 00:52:17,860
- No, I didn't...

980
00:52:17,860 --> 00:52:20,150
What am I supposed to think, Andrew?

981
00:52:20,150 --> 00:52:22,160
This all sounds crazy...

982
00:52:22,160 --> 00:52:24,370
I cannot believe that Dr. Benderfax...

983
00:52:24,370 --> 00:52:26,580
would do those things.

984
00:52:26,580 --> 00:52:27,990
- Carmen, do you really think...

985
00:52:27,990 --> 00:52:30,160
that I would make something like this up?

986
00:52:30,660 --> 00:52:33,620
- People have tried to
infiltrate the Institute before...

987
00:52:33,750 --> 00:52:35,670
How can I be sure that you--

988
00:52:35,670 --> 00:52:37,300
- Please, Carmen!

989
00:52:37,300 --> 00:52:38,960
I am not a fanatic!

990
00:52:40,630 --> 00:52:42,930
I am not a fanatic...

991
00:52:42,930 --> 00:52:44,010
I know that...

992
00:52:44,010 --> 00:52:46,140
everything I'm saying...

993
00:52:46,140 --> 00:52:48,060
may sound crazy...

994
00:52:48,060 --> 00:52:49,470
but it's true...

995
00:52:49,470 --> 00:52:50,810
it's true...

996
00:52:50,810 --> 00:52:52,640
It's terrible...

997
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:54,310
but it's true.

998
00:52:55,520 --> 00:52:58,400
- I want to believe you, Andrew...but I can't.

999
00:52:59,030 --> 00:53:02,490
- Carmen, Dr. Benderfax is killing people...

1000
00:53:02,490 --> 00:53:03,860
We have got to stop him...

1001
00:53:03,860 --> 00:53:07,120
before he kills again.

1002
00:53:08,950 --> 00:53:11,080
- You'd better leave now, Andrew...

1003
00:53:11,080 --> 00:53:13,080
I need some time to think.

1004
00:53:14,960 --> 00:53:16,790
- Fine.

1005
00:53:16,790 --> 00:53:18,790
Think!

1006
00:53:21,590 --> 00:53:24,680
(suspenseful music)

1007
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:32,520
(Andrew grunting)

1008
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:47,410
(intense music)

1009
00:54:08,190 --> 00:54:10,810
(knocking)

1010
00:54:12,770 --> 00:54:15,730
(slow suspenseful music)

1011
00:54:19,270 --> 00:54:20,360
- Horrible.

1012
00:54:21,150 --> 00:54:23,150
- His name is Vincent Grider...

1013
00:54:23,150 --> 00:54:26,280
We found him like this
in his apartment this morning...

1014
00:54:26,900 --> 00:54:30,830
What would make a person do
something like this, Dr. Benderfax?

1015
00:54:32,910 --> 00:54:34,370
- Well, Detective...

1016
00:54:34,870 --> 00:54:37,370
My field is neurology, not psychiatry...

1017
00:54:37,370 --> 00:54:39,830
but I would say...no one thing...

1018
00:54:39,830 --> 00:54:41,170
It could be a combination of...

1019
00:54:41,170 --> 00:54:43,750
instability...genetic flaws...

1020
00:54:43,750 --> 00:54:45,130
paranoid thinking...

1021
00:54:45,130 --> 00:54:48,050
perhaps, latent schizophrenia...

1022
00:54:48,050 --> 00:54:50,470
repressed rage and hatred...

1023
00:54:50,470 --> 00:54:53,310
all combining with some...

1024
00:54:53,310 --> 00:54:55,560
drastic happening to drive a person...

1025
00:54:55,560 --> 00:54:57,890
over the edge!

1026
00:54:57,890 --> 00:54:59,600
Do you have a suspect?

1027
00:55:00,350 --> 00:55:02,440
- As a matter of fact, we've identified...

1028
00:55:02,440 --> 00:55:05,320
the fingerprints of one of
your staff at the crime scene...

1029
00:55:05,320 --> 00:55:07,370
a Dr. Andrew March.

1030
00:55:07,820 --> 00:55:10,030
- Are you suggesting that Andrew?

1031
00:55:10,030 --> 00:55:13,700
- Were you aware that Dr. March
filed a police report on you last night...

1032
00:55:13,700 --> 00:55:15,370
Dr. Benderfax?

1033
00:55:15,370 --> 00:55:17,330
- A report on me?

1034
00:55:17,330 --> 00:55:18,830
Whatever for?

1035
00:55:18,830 --> 00:55:21,080
- March claimed you were
using patients here for...

1036
00:55:21,080 --> 00:55:22,920
terminal experiments!

1037
00:55:22,920 --> 00:55:25,450
He wanted me to shut your operation down.

1038
00:55:26,210 --> 00:55:27,840
- Absurd!

1039
00:55:27,840 --> 00:55:30,260
- Yeah, that's pretty much what I told him...

1040
00:55:30,260 --> 00:55:32,850
Then, this morning we find Mr. Grider, here...

1041
00:55:32,850 --> 00:55:35,310
and I figured I'd better talk to ya.

1042
00:55:35,850 --> 00:55:38,270
- Surely, you don't suspect me?

1043
00:55:38,350 --> 00:55:39,690
- No, Doctor...

1044
00:55:40,770 --> 00:55:43,560
But I think March could
be trying to set you up.

1045
00:55:44,820 --> 00:55:46,360
- Set me up?

1046
00:55:46,360 --> 00:55:48,110
But why?

1047
00:55:48,360 --> 00:55:50,780
- That was my next question, Doctor.

1048
00:55:50,780 --> 00:55:52,950
- [Benderfax] I really wouldn't know.

1049
00:55:53,260 --> 00:55:56,450
I just hired Andrew a couple of days ago...

1050
00:55:56,450 --> 00:55:58,410
He has excellent credentials...

1051
00:55:58,410 --> 00:56:01,500
and he's a very fine medical illustrator.

1052
00:56:01,500 --> 00:56:02,630
- [Detective] Oh...

1053
00:56:02,630 --> 00:56:05,920
Do you have any examples
of March's illustrations?

1054
00:56:06,590 --> 00:56:08,300
- Why, yes...

1055
00:56:08,300 --> 00:56:11,430
I have some of his drawings right here...

1056
00:56:17,350 --> 00:56:19,680
[Benderfax] There you are, Detective.

1057
00:56:19,850 --> 00:56:23,230
(suspenseful music)

1058
00:56:23,230 --> 00:56:25,650
- March did this?

1059
00:56:25,650 --> 00:56:27,860
- [Benderfax] That's right.

1060
00:56:28,900 --> 00:56:30,570
- Tell me, Doctor...

1061
00:56:30,570 --> 00:56:32,280
do you have any reason to think...

1062
00:56:32,280 --> 00:56:35,990
March would want to move
from dogs to humans?

1063
00:56:36,280 --> 00:56:38,330
- I'd never have guessed it...

1064
00:56:38,330 --> 00:56:42,120
He seems like such a nice young man...

1065
00:56:42,120 --> 00:56:44,920
but you never can tell, can you?

1066
00:56:46,040 --> 00:56:47,420
Is he under arrest?

1067
00:56:47,420 --> 00:56:50,460
- [Detective] We've had an A.P.B.
out on him for a few hours...

1068
00:56:50,760 --> 00:56:52,510
But don't worry...

1069
00:56:52,510 --> 00:56:54,590
we'll find him...

1070
00:56:55,850 --> 00:56:58,310
Can I take this drawing with me, Doctor?

1071
00:56:58,310 --> 00:57:00,770
- Please take them all.

1072
00:57:01,180 --> 00:57:04,060
- I appreciate your cooperation, Sir.

1073
00:57:04,650 --> 00:57:07,940
- Anything to help the police, Detective.

1074
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:11,990
(suspenseful music)

1075
00:57:26,820 --> 00:57:31,820
(sad piano music)
(duck quacks)

1076
00:58:01,080 --> 00:58:03,160
- Vincent...

1077
00:58:04,480 --> 00:58:06,830
Vincent!

1078
00:58:09,040 --> 00:58:11,380
(duck quacks)

1079
00:58:11,380 --> 00:58:13,510
(dramatic upbeat music)

1080
00:58:25,390 --> 00:58:28,310
(phone rings)

1081
00:58:43,330 --> 00:58:44,450
- Hello.

1082
00:58:44,700 --> 00:58:46,870
- Hello, Carmen...

1083
00:58:46,870 --> 00:58:49,920
I hope I haven't caught you at a bad time...

1084
00:58:49,920 --> 00:58:52,750
You haven't been answering the phone, dear.

1085
00:58:53,000 --> 00:58:54,300
- Dr. Benderfax...

1086
00:58:54,300 --> 00:58:56,220
I'm sorry...I was in the shower.

1087
00:58:56,370 --> 00:58:57,720
- Ah...

1088
00:58:57,720 --> 00:58:59,550
Nothing like a steamy shower...

1089
00:58:59,550 --> 00:59:01,470
as therapy for the conscience...

1090
00:59:01,470 --> 00:59:03,260
my father always used to say.

1091
00:59:03,260 --> 00:59:06,390
- Come on...Carmen...Get off the phone.
(dramatic upbeat music)

1092
00:59:15,650 --> 00:59:18,110
- What can I do for you, Dr. Benderfax?

1093
00:59:18,110 --> 00:59:19,070
- Carmen...

1094
00:59:19,070 --> 00:59:20,910
I need you to come into the Institute...

1095
00:59:20,910 --> 00:59:23,700
and meet me in my office, immediately.

1096
00:59:24,080 --> 00:59:25,490
- What's wrong, Sir?

1097
00:59:25,490 --> 00:59:28,530
- I'm afraid I can't discuss
it on the phone, Carmen...

1098
00:59:28,530 --> 00:59:30,790
Get here as quickly as you can...

1099
00:59:30,790 --> 00:59:32,460
I'll explain everything in detail...

1100
00:59:32,460 --> 00:59:34,420
when you arrive.

1101
00:59:35,380 --> 00:59:37,210
- All right, Dr. Benderfax...

1102
00:59:37,210 --> 00:59:39,470
I'll leave now, if it's that important.

1103
00:59:39,760 --> 00:59:41,840
- Thank you, Carmen...

1104
00:59:41,840 --> 00:59:44,380
I wouldn't ask you, if it wasn't.

1105
00:59:44,510 --> 00:59:46,770
- Yes, Sir.

1106
00:59:50,390 --> 00:59:51,770
(dramatic upbeat music)

1107
01:00:05,600 --> 01:00:07,580
(engine revs)

1108
01:00:14,130 --> 01:00:16,090
(dramatic upbeat music)

1109
01:00:37,520 --> 01:00:39,890
(Farance screams)

1110
01:00:39,890 --> 01:00:42,310
(bike crashes loudly)

1111
01:00:49,410 --> 01:00:50,790
(sighs)

1112
01:00:54,750 --> 01:00:57,040
(music fades)

1113
01:00:57,040 --> 01:00:59,340
- [Andrew] I'm really sorry
about that, Farance...

1114
01:00:59,340 --> 01:01:01,470
Are you sure you don't
want to go to the hospital?

1115
01:01:01,470 --> 01:01:03,510
- No...No, forget about it...

1116
01:01:03,510 --> 01:01:05,050
But I have something to tell you.

1117
01:01:05,340 --> 01:01:06,300
- What is it?

1118
01:01:06,300 --> 01:01:08,890
- I overheard a detective taking to...

1119
01:01:08,890 --> 01:01:11,310
Dr. Benderfax at the Institute today...

1120
01:01:11,310 --> 01:01:14,400
He seemed to think you killed
an old man named, Grider.

1121
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:16,900
- Vincent Grider?

1122
01:01:16,900 --> 01:01:18,610
Oh, my God!

1123
01:01:18,650 --> 01:01:20,610
- The detective said he has
an A.P.B. out on you...

1124
01:01:20,610 --> 01:01:22,590
so you might not want
to be driving around.

1125
01:01:22,590 --> 01:01:24,110
- But I didn't do it Farance.

1126
01:01:24,110 --> 01:01:25,950
- That's not what the police think.

1127
01:01:27,160 --> 01:01:28,200
- Great...

1128
01:01:28,200 --> 01:01:30,990
First, Wilma is mutilated
in Benderfax's lab...

1129
01:01:30,990 --> 01:01:32,750
and now this!

1130
01:01:32,750 --> 01:01:35,370
- You were in Benderfax's lab?

1131
01:01:35,370 --> 01:01:36,750
- Farance...

1132
01:01:36,750 --> 01:01:39,340
what do you know about the lab?

1133
01:01:39,840 --> 01:01:41,300
- My place is not too far up here...

1134
01:01:41,300 --> 01:01:44,720
You can hide the car there
for awhile, if you want to.

1135
01:01:49,220 --> 01:01:51,560
(music fades)

1136
01:01:56,810 --> 01:01:58,110
- Nice closet, Farance.

1137
01:01:58,110 --> 01:02:00,480
- [man's voice] Dog data! No...No...

1138
01:02:00,480 --> 01:02:01,530
- [Andrew] What was that?

1139
01:02:01,530 --> 01:02:02,900
- Blitz.

1140
01:02:02,900 --> 01:02:04,490
- [Blitz] Dog...Dog...Dog...

1141
01:02:04,490 --> 01:02:07,360
- Whoa, hold on. You mean the guy
who broke into Benderfax's lab?

1142
01:02:07,360 --> 01:02:08,240
- Uh huh.

1143
01:02:08,240 --> 01:02:09,450
(Blitz mumbling)

1144
01:02:09,450 --> 01:02:10,440
- [Andrew] He's up there?

1145
01:02:10,440 --> 01:02:11,290
- [Blitz] No...No...

1146
01:02:11,290 --> 01:02:12,450
- Yeah...

1147
01:02:13,540 --> 01:02:14,750
You go on up...

1148
01:02:15,250 --> 01:02:18,210
I'm gonna wait down here...
if you don't mind.

1149
01:02:19,590 --> 01:02:21,130
- [Blitz] No...No...

1150
01:02:21,130 --> 01:02:22,500
(papers rustling)

1151
01:02:25,840 --> 01:02:28,220
- Blitz?
- [Blitz] Dog...data...

1152
01:02:28,220 --> 01:02:30,760
Can you hand me that notebook over there?

1153
01:02:30,760 --> 01:02:32,100
- Yeah...

1154
01:02:32,100 --> 01:02:33,060
Which one?

1155
01:02:33,270 --> 01:02:36,100
- 21...The one sticking out...number 21...

1156
01:02:39,350 --> 01:02:41,730
No...dogs...dogs...dogs...

1157
01:02:41,730 --> 01:02:42,840
Dog data!

1158
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:44,220
This is nothing but dog data!

1159
01:02:44,220 --> 01:02:46,490
I've wasted a whole afternoon on this!

1160
01:02:46,490 --> 01:02:48,610
Did you want something, or what?

1161
01:02:48,610 --> 01:02:49,110
- Blitz...

1162
01:02:49,110 --> 01:02:51,240
- I know what Benderfax is doing in his lab...
- [Blitz] No...no...

1163
01:02:51,240 --> 01:02:55,020
I found one of my patients...
mutilated on his operating table!

1164
01:02:55,020 --> 01:02:56,660
- No...no...

1165
01:02:56,660 --> 01:02:57,580
- Blitz!

1166
01:02:57,580 --> 01:02:58,900
Blitz, I need your help...

1167
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:00,420
You have evidence against Benderfax...

1168
01:03:00,420 --> 01:03:02,340
the notes that you took out of his lab!

1169
01:03:02,340 --> 01:03:05,550
(suspenseful music)

1170
01:03:20,980 --> 01:03:21,860
Blitz...

1171
01:03:21,860 --> 01:03:23,400
What'd you find out in these lab notes?

1172
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:24,270
I mean...

1173
01:03:24,270 --> 01:03:27,320
What's Benderfax doing down there?
Who's involved? Martin? Clench?

1174
01:03:27,860 --> 01:03:28,990
- Nurse Clench...

1175
01:03:28,990 --> 01:03:31,660
She assisted Dr. Benderfax
in his research, for years...

1176
01:03:31,660 --> 01:03:33,250
In one experiment, Nurse Clench...

1177
01:03:33,250 --> 01:03:34,830
amputated the arms and legs of...

1178
01:03:34,830 --> 01:03:38,370
mother chimps with newborn babies...
to see how they'd cope...emotionally...

1179
01:03:38,370 --> 01:03:41,040
Grief studies...yeah...
They called 'em grief studies!

1180
01:03:41,040 --> 01:03:43,050
Nurse Clench repeated
the experiment for a year...

1181
01:03:43,050 --> 01:03:45,050
and it was a complete success!

1182
01:03:45,050 --> 01:03:46,850
Consistently, the babies died of neglect...

1183
01:03:46,850 --> 01:03:49,800
and the mothers became catatonic...
and died of starvation...

1184
01:03:49,800 --> 01:03:51,590
despite intravenous feeding...

1185
01:03:51,590 --> 01:03:55,100
That bitch helped take the study of grief
right into the 21st Century!

1186
01:03:55,100 --> 01:03:57,020
Something to be proud of...don't you think?

1187
01:03:57,020 --> 01:03:59,560
(suspenseful music)

1188
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:21,000
- Blitz...what about human experiments?

1189
01:04:21,370 --> 01:04:25,630
- Human subjects are not readily available
for Benderfax's types of experiments...

1190
01:04:25,630 --> 01:04:28,710
That's why he took over the East Hill
Mental Hospital, 10 years ago...

1191
01:04:28,710 --> 01:04:31,130
and changed the name
to the Benderfax Institute...

1192
01:04:31,130 --> 01:04:35,510
It gave him a virtual warehouse
of societal rejects to choose from...

1193
01:04:35,510 --> 01:04:37,100
He had control of their records...

1194
01:04:37,100 --> 01:04:38,890
and nobody seems to miss 'em...

1195
01:04:38,890 --> 01:04:41,440
Wow! What a great setup!

1196
01:04:41,440 --> 01:04:43,440
(suspenseful music)

1197
01:05:04,040 --> 01:05:06,380
- So, he's definitely
experimenting on the patients?

1198
01:05:06,380 --> 01:05:08,000
- Oh...Well that's all he does...

1199
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:09,500
I mean, he keeps a few
dogs and cats around...

1200
01:05:09,500 --> 01:05:12,760
just in case the state inspector
might want to check out the facility...

1201
01:05:12,760 --> 01:05:14,990
I mean, he fakes all the
animal research data...

1202
01:05:14,990 --> 01:05:16,990
to keep the grant money rolling in...

1203
01:05:16,990 --> 01:05:18,720
You can't run a lab without cash...

1204
01:05:19,060 --> 01:05:21,560
You can't run a lab without cash!

1205
01:05:21,560 --> 01:05:23,070
You got a cigarette Doctor?

1206
01:05:23,070 --> 01:05:24,850
(loud crash)

1207
01:05:25,400 --> 01:05:27,360
(tense music)

1208
01:05:34,660 --> 01:05:36,370
- Hey, Farance...

1209
01:05:36,370 --> 01:05:38,280
I want to talk to you about this...

1210
01:05:38,280 --> 01:05:41,290
(electric guitar song)

1211
01:05:43,910 --> 01:05:46,330
I thought we were friends, Farance...

1212
01:05:46,330 --> 01:05:48,670
Is that the way you treat a friend?

1213
01:05:48,670 --> 01:05:51,670
Bash 'em in the skull
with a frigging baseball bat?

1214
01:05:51,670 --> 01:05:54,010
I don't think so, Farance...

1215
01:05:55,970 --> 01:05:59,850
I think I need to square
this situation up, Farance...

1216
01:05:59,850 --> 01:06:01,860
It's only fair...Don't you think?

1217
01:06:03,130 --> 01:06:05,600
Don't you agree...
I have reasonable cause to want to...

1218
01:06:05,600 --> 01:06:08,480
blow your frigging head off...
You little freak?

1219
01:06:10,820 --> 01:06:12,480
[Martin] I know you're here, Farance.

1220
01:06:12,480 --> 01:06:13,490
- [Farance] Come on...

1221
01:06:13,490 --> 01:06:15,740
- [Martin] I can hear you pissing your pants!

1222
01:06:15,740 --> 01:06:17,450
- [Farance] Bastard...

1223
01:06:17,450 --> 01:06:19,160
(rattling door handle)

1224
01:06:19,160 --> 01:06:20,860
- Found you, you little shit!

1225
01:06:20,860 --> 01:06:23,700
(gasps)

1226
01:06:24,200 --> 01:06:25,540
(bat thuds to floor)

1227
01:06:25,540 --> 01:06:27,330
Geez, Farance!

1228
01:06:27,330 --> 01:06:29,230
What a pitiful little pansy!

1229
01:06:29,540 --> 01:06:30,790
(Blitz laughs)

1230
01:06:31,550 --> 01:06:33,090
- Laugh it up, fuzz-ball!

1231
01:06:33,090 --> 01:06:35,220
(gun shots)

1232
01:06:37,010 --> 01:06:39,220
Jesus Christ!

1233
01:06:39,220 --> 01:06:41,090
(tense music)

1234
01:06:54,690 --> 01:06:56,860
[Martin] Weird...

1235
01:06:57,200 --> 01:06:59,990
(phone rings)

1236
01:07:04,200 --> 01:07:05,250
- Benderfax...

1237
01:07:05,330 --> 01:07:08,250
- Doc...I tailed Farance, like you told me to....

1238
01:07:08,250 --> 01:07:12,420
Turns out that little freak's been
hiding Clarence Blitz up in his attic...

1239
01:07:12,420 --> 01:07:14,880
Looks like he's been living
up there for quite awhile.

1240
01:07:15,210 --> 01:07:16,300
- Really?

1241
01:07:16,300 --> 01:07:18,260
How very convenient...

1242
01:07:18,260 --> 01:07:21,830
I assume you've...spoken with them both?

1243
01:07:21,830 --> 01:07:21,850
- Yeah, Doc...
I assume you've...spoken with them both?

1244
01:07:21,850 --> 01:07:23,010
- Yeah, Doc...

1245
01:07:23,010 --> 01:07:25,680
I gave 'em both a real good talking to.

1246
01:07:25,680 --> 01:07:27,890
- Splendid...

1247
01:07:27,890 --> 01:07:31,520
And have you by any chance come
across our young Dr. March, today?

1248
01:07:31,520 --> 01:07:32,770
- March?

1249
01:07:32,770 --> 01:07:33,610
No...

1250
01:07:33,610 --> 01:07:34,690
Not yet...

1251
01:07:34,690 --> 01:07:36,190
But don't you worry, Doc...

1252
01:07:36,190 --> 01:07:37,990
I'll find that pencil neck.

1253
01:07:37,990 --> 01:07:39,150
- You just did, asshole!

1254
01:07:39,150 --> 01:07:40,030
(bat thuds)

1255
01:07:40,030 --> 01:07:42,200
(loud crash)

1256
01:07:43,490 --> 01:07:44,830
Benderfax!

1257
01:07:44,830 --> 01:07:46,580
You've gone too far this time!

1258
01:07:46,580 --> 01:07:49,000
- I'd like to speak to you at leisure, Doctor...

1259
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:52,750
but you see, I'm presently in a
meeting with one of my nurses...

1260
01:07:52,750 --> 01:07:54,710
Carmen Snow...

1261
01:07:54,710 --> 01:07:56,050
Perhaps you've met...

1262
01:07:56,380 --> 01:07:59,090
You're very welcome to
drop by my lab sometime...

1263
01:07:59,090 --> 01:08:02,050
and we can continue this
discussion in person...

1264
01:08:02,050 --> 01:08:04,260
Goodbye, Doctor.

1265
01:08:04,260 --> 01:08:06,060
- Carmen! Carmen!

1266
01:08:06,600 --> 01:08:07,850
- Well, now...

1267
01:08:07,850 --> 01:08:11,140
Where were we, my dear?

1268
01:08:19,860 --> 01:08:20,820
- Farance...

1269
01:08:21,860 --> 01:08:23,980
(groans)

1270
01:08:25,950 --> 01:08:27,700
Don't move.

1271
01:08:28,410 --> 01:08:30,830
(groans)

1272
01:08:33,130 --> 01:08:35,290
- It's very kind of you, Carmen...

1273
01:08:35,290 --> 01:08:37,340
to want to spare my feelings...

1274
01:08:37,340 --> 01:08:39,420
but you must try to understand...

1275
01:08:39,420 --> 01:08:43,030
that Andrew March is a
loathsome, conniving man...

1276
01:08:43,030 --> 01:08:46,260
with no sense of morality, whatsoever...

1277
01:08:46,260 --> 01:08:50,100
He would do absolutely
anything to destroy me...

1278
01:08:50,100 --> 01:08:53,630
even becoming close to you, Carmen...

1279
01:08:53,630 --> 01:08:57,690
with the intention of manipulating
your opinions of me...

1280
01:08:57,690 --> 01:09:01,400
Andrew did try to turn you against me...

1281
01:09:01,400 --> 01:09:03,570
Isn't that true?

1282
01:09:04,980 --> 01:09:07,490
- Andrew said that he went
into your laboratory...

1283
01:09:07,490 --> 01:09:09,700
He said that he found the
new patient, Wilma...

1284
01:09:09,700 --> 01:09:12,080
mutilated on the operating table.

1285
01:09:12,080 --> 01:09:13,290
- I see.

1286
01:09:13,290 --> 01:09:16,670
- He said that she had been operated on...
while she was still alive...

1287
01:09:16,670 --> 01:09:19,210
that you had been experimenting on her...
(suspenseful music)

1288
01:09:20,090 --> 01:09:21,420
I'm sorry, Sir...

1289
01:09:21,420 --> 01:09:23,510
I know I should I have told you before...

1290
01:09:23,510 --> 01:09:25,590
I'm so sorry.

1291
01:09:25,590 --> 01:09:27,850
- Here you are, my dear.

1292
01:09:27,850 --> 01:09:29,100
- Thank you, Sir.

1293
01:09:29,100 --> 01:09:31,210
- That's a good girl...

1294
01:09:31,210 --> 01:09:33,900
Go ahead and get it all out.

1295
01:09:35,230 --> 01:09:38,570
- I didn't believe him, Dr. Benderfax...

1296
01:09:38,570 --> 01:09:40,190
I hope you believe me...

1297
01:09:40,190 --> 01:09:42,570
I know you would have
never done those things.

1298
01:09:42,570 --> 01:09:45,030
- No...Of course not, Carmen...

1299
01:09:45,030 --> 01:09:46,660
Of course not...

1300
01:09:46,950 --> 01:09:51,100
If only I had more employees...
as loyal as you, Carmen...

1301
01:09:51,330 --> 01:09:54,870
You're truly an asset to the Institute...

1302
01:09:55,370 --> 01:09:58,880
I'm very proud to have hired you.

1303
01:09:58,880 --> 01:10:00,590
- Thank you, Dr. Benderfax...

1304
01:10:00,590 --> 01:10:02,670
I'm happy that you feel that way.

1305
01:10:04,340 --> 01:10:06,680
- Oh...I do, Carmen....

1306
01:10:07,640 --> 01:10:10,810
I truly do...

1307
01:10:10,810 --> 01:10:12,970
(dramatic music)

1308
01:10:19,440 --> 01:10:21,920
(suspenseful music)

1309
01:10:23,030 --> 01:10:25,950
- [Benderfax] I'm truly sorry
it's come to this, my dear...

1310
01:10:26,280 --> 01:10:29,160
but you've been conspiring against me...

1311
01:10:29,160 --> 01:10:31,030
and I simply cannot be expected...

1312
01:10:31,030 --> 01:10:33,120
to tolerate this kind of disloyalty...

1313
01:10:33,120 --> 01:10:35,460
from a member of my own staff...

1314
01:10:35,790 --> 01:10:38,630
Oh...I've seen you whispering in the corridors...

1315
01:10:38,630 --> 01:10:41,040
with that deviant, Farance Wur...

1316
01:10:41,290 --> 01:10:42,880
and you made no secret of your...

1317
01:10:42,880 --> 01:10:46,220
extracurricular activities with Dr. March...

1318
01:10:46,220 --> 01:10:48,050
Did you think I couldn't put...

1319
01:10:48,050 --> 01:10:51,050
two and two together?

1320
01:10:52,010 --> 01:10:54,100
(dramatic music)

1321
01:11:02,820 --> 01:11:07,200
(machinery beeps)
(suspenseful music)

1322
01:11:07,400 --> 01:11:11,950
Subject K27...white female...
age 24...excellent health...

1323
01:11:11,950 --> 01:11:13,740
For this subject I've
placed the sensor probes...

1324
01:11:13,740 --> 01:11:17,410
behind the ocular orbits in an attempt...
to reduce brain activity interference...

1325
01:11:17,410 --> 01:11:19,370
encountered in previous operations...

1326
01:11:19,540 --> 01:11:22,500
There is minor bleeding...
but minimal tissue damage...

1327
01:11:22,500 --> 01:11:25,670
If all goes well...Carmen's pretty eyes...

1328
01:11:25,670 --> 01:11:28,800
will not be harmed in any way.

1329
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:30,800
(dramatic music)

1330
01:11:38,560 --> 01:11:40,270
Larry...What are you doing?
(all yelling)

1331
01:11:40,270 --> 01:11:43,270
Get...Get off!
(all yelling)

1332
01:11:43,270 --> 01:11:45,070
Larry! Get...
(all yelling)

1333
01:11:45,070 --> 01:11:46,990
(all yelling)

1334
01:11:46,990 --> 01:11:49,070
Get off me! No!
(all yelling)

1335
01:11:49,070 --> 01:11:52,280
Let...go! Get off!
(all yelling)

1336
01:11:52,280 --> 01:11:53,070
(all yelling)

1337
01:11:55,700 --> 01:11:57,750
Larry!

1338
01:12:02,710 --> 01:12:05,880
(tense music)

1339
01:12:08,920 --> 01:12:11,340
(breaths heavily)

1340
01:12:14,010 --> 01:12:16,510
- Oh, flesh....

1341
01:12:17,770 --> 01:12:20,850
the bliss of it...

1342
01:12:21,980 --> 01:12:23,650
- Dr. Benderfax...

1343
01:12:23,650 --> 01:12:25,450
Where are you?

1344
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:28,230
- I'm right here, Carmen.

1345
01:12:28,230 --> 01:12:30,110
- What's happening?

1346
01:12:30,110 --> 01:12:31,240
- My dear...

1347
01:12:31,240 --> 01:12:34,780
the time has come for us
to get to know each other...

1348
01:12:34,780 --> 01:12:38,200
in a more intimate way.

1349
01:12:38,370 --> 01:12:40,580
(dramatic music)

1350
01:12:42,540 --> 01:12:44,540
(machinery beeps)
(tense music)

1351
01:12:47,550 --> 01:12:50,420
(breaths heavily)

1352
01:12:51,340 --> 01:12:54,340
Oh, Carmen...

1353
01:12:56,390 --> 01:13:00,270
Wonderfully healthy organs...

1354
01:13:00,270 --> 01:13:02,060
(sighs)

1355
01:13:02,440 --> 01:13:04,440
(dramatic music)

1356
01:13:08,650 --> 01:13:10,240
(machinery beeps)
(tense music)

1357
01:13:11,280 --> 01:13:14,280
(ethereal music)

1358
01:13:16,700 --> 01:13:19,290
Can you feel it, Carmen?

1359
01:13:19,290 --> 01:13:23,120
The Telefaximial Field...(gasps)

1360
01:13:23,120 --> 01:13:27,040
It's incredible...

1361
01:13:27,040 --> 01:13:30,590
It's beautiful...

1362
01:13:31,710 --> 01:13:34,340
(ethereal music)

1363
01:14:12,460 --> 01:14:15,010
(machine loudly prints)

1364
01:14:15,010 --> 01:14:17,180
(music fades)

1365
01:14:19,220 --> 01:14:21,140
(laughs)

1366
01:14:21,220 --> 01:14:22,520
Fantastic!

1367
01:14:22,520 --> 01:14:25,140
Exactly as I visualized it!

1368
01:14:28,440 --> 01:14:30,610
- You bastard...What have you done?

1369
01:14:30,630 --> 01:14:34,360
- Andrew, you won't believe all that's
happened, since we last spoke.

1370
01:14:34,360 --> 01:14:35,700
- You lousy--

1371
01:14:35,700 --> 01:14:37,490
- This isn't a pair of forceps, Andrew...

1372
01:14:37,490 --> 01:14:39,560
so please stay where you are.

1373
01:14:39,560 --> 01:14:41,240
- You'll never get away with this, Benderfax!

1374
01:14:41,240 --> 01:14:42,490
- Oh, but I will, Andrew...

1375
01:14:42,490 --> 01:14:45,410
You see, I've just made the
greatest breakthrough of my career...

1376
01:14:45,410 --> 01:14:46,830
You see that printout?

1377
01:14:47,330 --> 01:14:49,630
It's my dog...Boxy!

1378
01:14:49,630 --> 01:14:52,250
A perfect reproduction of
my own visualized thought...

1379
01:14:52,250 --> 01:14:54,760
telepathically transmitted from my brain...

1380
01:14:54,760 --> 01:14:56,840
to Carmen's interior organs...

1381
01:14:56,840 --> 01:14:59,550
then relayed from her brain
to these probes...

1382
01:14:59,550 --> 01:15:02,540
which feeds the telepathic
data to my computer here...

1383
01:15:02,540 --> 01:15:05,430
which first amplifies, then
reproduces my thought picture...

1384
01:15:05,430 --> 01:15:08,270
into hard copy form...
and there you have it...

1385
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:09,650
Boxy!

1386
01:15:09,650 --> 01:15:11,610
I've finally done it!

1387
01:15:11,610 --> 01:15:15,030
I've achieved true
telepathic Telefacsimile!

1388
01:15:15,030 --> 01:15:17,950
- So you have been killing your patients...

1389
01:15:17,950 --> 01:15:19,740
and now you've done this to Carmen...

1390
01:15:19,740 --> 01:15:22,240
just so you can send a psychic...

1391
01:15:22,240 --> 01:15:24,580
FAX of your dog?!?

1392
01:15:24,580 --> 01:15:25,910
- You idiot...

1393
01:15:25,910 --> 01:15:28,540
You're just like all the others
who criticize my work....

1394
01:15:28,540 --> 01:15:30,670
You suffer from
chronic short sightedness....

1395
01:15:30,670 --> 01:15:32,630
You attack me...
because I'm willing to do...

1396
01:15:32,630 --> 01:15:35,170
whatever it takes
to reach a scientific goal...

1397
01:15:35,260 --> 01:15:36,670
You know that I have achieved...

1398
01:15:36,670 --> 01:15:38,930
what you and the others like you
could never achieve...

1399
01:15:38,930 --> 01:15:40,220
Admit it...

1400
01:15:40,220 --> 01:15:42,760
You're jealous of me and my breakthrough!

1401
01:15:42,760 --> 01:15:46,350
- You are a sick, twisted bastard, Benderfax...

1402
01:15:46,350 --> 01:15:48,270
and you can bet...that this...this...

1403
01:15:48,270 --> 01:15:50,690
breakthrough is going to be your last! --

1404
01:15:50,690 --> 01:15:52,690
- Andrew...

1405
01:15:52,690 --> 01:15:54,570
- Carmen...

1406
01:15:54,570 --> 01:15:56,940
(dramatic music)

1407
01:15:56,940 --> 01:15:58,840
(gun shot)
(tense music)

1408
01:16:00,660 --> 01:16:04,160
(Andrew's blood squirts)

1409
01:16:04,910 --> 01:16:06,240
- Andrew...

1410
01:16:06,240 --> 01:16:08,080
Andrew...

1411
01:16:08,250 --> 01:16:10,370
- It's too bad, Andrew...

1412
01:16:10,370 --> 01:16:12,080
I honestly liked you...

1413
01:16:12,630 --> 01:16:16,000
I had even hoped we might
someday work together...

1414
01:16:16,000 --> 01:16:18,090
(tense music)

1415
01:16:18,090 --> 01:16:19,670
Sorry, Andrew...

1416
01:16:19,670 --> 01:16:22,680
but I'm afraid it's sacrifice time...

1417
01:16:22,680 --> 01:16:25,220
(Benderfax gasps)

1418
01:16:25,970 --> 01:16:28,520
Lavinia...why?

1419
01:16:28,520 --> 01:16:30,140
- I'm sorry, Thomas...

1420
01:16:30,140 --> 01:16:31,270
(thuds to floor)

1421
01:16:33,810 --> 01:16:36,110
This is all your fault, you know...

1422
01:16:36,690 --> 01:16:39,070
You should never have come here...

1423
01:16:39,070 --> 01:16:41,610
He's a brilliant scientist...
(Andrew's blood squirts)

1424
01:16:41,610 --> 01:16:43,780
a true visionary...
(Andrew's blood squirts)

1425
01:16:43,780 --> 01:16:45,620
You've no right to judge him...
(Andrew's blood squirts)

1426
01:16:45,620 --> 01:16:47,240
not by this...

1427
01:16:47,330 --> 01:16:49,500
He was never evil...

1428
01:16:49,500 --> 01:16:51,460
just ahead of his time...

1429
01:16:51,460 --> 01:16:53,330
There's a difference!

1430
01:16:53,330 --> 01:16:56,460
(Andrew's blood squirts)

1431
01:16:56,460 --> 01:16:59,670
(thuds to floor)
(Andrew's blood squirts)

1432
01:17:00,470 --> 01:17:03,050
(sad piano music)

1433
01:17:04,430 --> 01:17:08,390
For these past 10 years, I've taken
care of everything for you, Thomas...

1434
01:17:08,720 --> 01:17:10,930
chosen the best test subjects...

1435
01:17:10,930 --> 01:17:12,520
altered their records...

1436
01:17:12,520 --> 01:17:15,270
even dealt with their remains...
when you'd finished with them...

1437
01:17:15,270 --> 01:17:16,730
I did it all...

1438
01:17:16,730 --> 01:17:20,570
because I believed the work you
were doing here was important, and...

1439
01:17:21,440 --> 01:17:23,990
because I love you, Thomas...

1440
01:17:25,030 --> 01:17:28,030
I have from the beginning, you know...

1441
01:17:28,030 --> 01:17:30,870
Though, you've rarely had a kind word for me...

1442
01:17:30,870 --> 01:17:32,790
or my ideas...

1443
01:17:32,960 --> 01:17:36,380
Remember those grief studies
we did, years ago?

1444
01:17:36,380 --> 01:17:38,800
They were my idea, weren't they?

1445
01:17:38,800 --> 01:17:40,960
I even won a grant to do them...

1446
01:17:40,960 --> 01:17:43,470
but you didn't care...

1447
01:17:43,470 --> 01:17:45,090
You had to tell me...

1448
01:17:45,090 --> 01:17:48,600
that amputating the arms and legs
of 200 mother chimps...

1449
01:17:48,600 --> 01:17:50,680
was a stupid idea...

1450
01:17:50,680 --> 01:17:53,270
after I'd already done it!

1451
01:17:54,270 --> 01:17:55,520
Still...

1452
01:17:55,520 --> 01:17:58,520
I've remained loyal to you
all these years, Thomas...

1453
01:17:59,020 --> 01:18:00,270
but lately...

1454
01:18:00,270 --> 01:18:02,590
things have got out of hand...

1455
01:18:02,590 --> 01:18:04,070
and what we're doing here...

1456
01:18:04,070 --> 01:18:07,240
just doesn't feel right anymore...

1457
01:18:07,240 --> 01:18:09,300
so I'm going to make it right...

1458
01:18:10,910 --> 01:18:14,120
I know you can never
forgive me for this, Thomas...

1459
01:18:14,790 --> 01:18:17,330
but I can live with that.

1460
01:18:19,460 --> 01:18:22,460
(whirring drill)
(tense music)

1461
01:18:28,590 --> 01:18:30,590
(music and drill fade)

1462
01:18:38,440 --> 01:18:40,750
- Well, you folks wanted to see Benderfax.

1463
01:18:41,570 --> 01:18:43,480
- Has he spoken yet, Detective?

1464
01:18:43,480 --> 01:18:46,200
- Not a word, since the incident, a month ago.

1465
01:18:46,490 --> 01:18:48,280
- What's gonna happen to them now...

1466
01:18:48,280 --> 01:18:50,240
Benderfax and Nurse Clench?

1467
01:18:50,240 --> 01:18:51,410
- Don't worry, Doctor...

1468
01:18:51,830 --> 01:18:54,660
We got enough evidence to
keep them out of circulation...

1469
01:18:54,660 --> 01:18:57,540
for a very...very long time...

1470
01:18:57,540 --> 01:18:59,880
Not that Benderfax is
gonna be much of a threat...

1471
01:18:59,880 --> 01:19:02,420
after what Nurse Clench did to him.

1472
01:19:02,420 --> 01:19:05,050
- Did she say why she did it, Detective?

1473
01:19:05,050 --> 01:19:08,050
- Uh...Something about a chimp experiment...

1474
01:19:08,050 --> 01:19:10,220
I couldn't make much sense of it...

1475
01:19:11,050 --> 01:19:12,010
Oh, Doctor...

1476
01:19:12,010 --> 01:19:13,920
did I tell ya the good news?

1477
01:19:14,140 --> 01:19:15,850
- What? What news?

1478
01:19:15,850 --> 01:19:18,850
- You're aware that Benderfax
faked the animal experiments...

1479
01:19:18,850 --> 01:19:21,100
hadn't done any for years, right?

1480
01:19:21,100 --> 01:19:22,940
Well, after we picked up Benderfax...

1481
01:19:22,940 --> 01:19:24,820
I checked the Institutes kennels...

1482
01:19:24,820 --> 01:19:26,360
and there he was...

1483
01:19:26,360 --> 01:19:27,740
Murphy!

1484
01:19:27,740 --> 01:19:28,990
- Who?

1485
01:19:29,110 --> 01:19:31,530
- Murphy, my dog.

1486
01:19:31,530 --> 01:19:34,200
- Oh, oh yeah, yeah, yeah...Murphy.

1487
01:19:34,200 --> 01:19:36,100
- Boy, was he glad to see me...

1488
01:19:36,450 --> 01:19:38,460
Of course, he was understandably distraught...

1489
01:19:38,460 --> 01:19:41,540
but...uh...no worse for wear...

1490
01:19:41,540 --> 01:19:44,050
Here, look...I have a Polaroid of him.

1491
01:19:48,720 --> 01:19:51,550
- I'm glad that you got
your dog back, Detective...

1492
01:19:52,430 --> 01:19:54,720
- I just wish I could have
stopped Benderfax...

1493
01:19:54,720 --> 01:19:57,640
before he got to Katherine
and Vincent Grider...and...

1494
01:19:57,640 --> 01:20:00,230
all the other victims...

1495
01:20:00,230 --> 01:20:04,360
I feel like we were
helping him the whole time!

1496
01:20:04,360 --> 01:20:06,940
- Andrew, don't talk like that...

1497
01:20:06,940 --> 01:20:09,530
There's nothing we could have done...

1498
01:20:09,530 --> 01:20:12,370
At least it's over, now.

1499
01:20:12,370 --> 01:20:14,410
- Yeah, I guess it is...

1500
01:20:14,410 --> 01:20:16,950
for Benderfax, anyway!

1501
01:20:16,950 --> 01:20:18,950
(blood-chilling music)

1502
01:20:20,790 --> 01:20:22,330
- [Benderfax] Morons!

1503
01:20:22,330 --> 01:20:25,840
(dramatic music)
(laboratory machinery beeps)

